===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|en|ang|ynce}}, a {{bor|en|la|uncia||twelfth part|nocap=1}}. {{doublet|lang=en|ounce}}.

====Noun====
{{en-noun|es}}

# A unit of [[length]] equal to one [[twelfth]] of a [[foot]], or exactly 2.54 [[centimetre]]s.
# {{lb|en|meteorology}} The amount of water which would cover a surface to the depth of an inch, used as a measurement of [[rainfall]].
# The amount of an alcoholic beverage which would fill a glass or bottle to the depth of an inch.
# {{lb|en|figuratively}} A very short distance.
#: ''"Don't move an '''inch'''!"''
#* Shakespeare
#*: Beldame, I think we watched you at an '''inch'''.

